  day          = {20},
  url          = {https://www.phenomenalworld.org/analysis/family-business/},
  note         = {Traces the structural recomposition of the Indian corporate sector 2000--2020: the disintegration of the traditional Large Business Houses; the rise of the ``New Capitalists'' (Ambani/Reliance, Adani, Jindals, Mittal, Agarwal, Hindujas); the 2003--2011 debt-fuelled boom financed by state-owned banks; the centralisation of capital through the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code 2016; and the rejection of the ``crony capitalism'' framing in favour of a deeper reading of state-capital fusion under what Banaji, following Paul Mattick, calls ``state-aided private capital development.''}
}

